# E2E Test Organization - MANDATORY Rules

**⚠️ CRITICAL: Always reference [`apps/web/__tests__/e2e/TEST_GUIDELINES.md`](../../apps/web/__tests__/e2e/TEST_GUIDELINES.md) when planning, creating, or finishing E2E tests.**

## Core Principles (MANDATORY)

1. **One Folder Per Page/Feature** - Each page gets its own directory: `__tests__/e2e/[feature-name]/`
2. **One TEST_PLAN.md Per Page** - Single doc with plan, checklist, status tracking, issues log, execution history
3. **Test Files Only** - No reports, summaries, or redundant docs in page folders (archive to `_archive/`)
4. **Clean Structure** - Only `TEST_PLAN.md` + `[page-name].e2e.ts` in each page folder

## Required Folder Structure

```
__tests__/e2e/
├── TEST_GUIDELINES.md           # ⚠️ ALWAYS REFERENCE THIS FIRST
├── helpers/                     # Shared utilities
├── [feature-name]/              # One folder per page
│   ├── TEST_PLAN.md            # Single doc: plan + tracking
│   └── [feature-name].e2e.ts   # Test file only
└── _archive/                    # Old reports (archived)
```

## TEST_PLAN.md Template (MUST Follow)

Every `TEST_PLAN.md` must include these sections:
- **📊 Test Status Overview** (table: Category | Tests | Status)
- **🎯 Critical Priority Tests** (checklist)
- **✅ Test Checklist** (all test cases)
- **🐛 Issues Log** (table: ID | Description | Status | Priority)
- **📈 Test Execution History** (table: Date | Tester | Results | Notes)
- **🎯 Next Steps**

## Workflow (MANDATORY)

### When Creating New Test Suite
1. **Reference TEST_GUIDELINES.md** first
2. Create folder: `__tests__/e2e/[feature-name]/`
3. Create `TEST_PLAN.md` using template
4. Create test file: `[feature-name].e2e.ts`
5. Document test cases in TEST_PLAN.md (planning phase)
6. Implement tests in `.e2e.ts`
7. Update status in TEST_PLAN.md as tests are completed

### When Adding Tests
1. Add test case to TEST_PLAN.md checklist
2. Implement test in `.e2e.ts`
3. Update status table in TEST_PLAN.md
4. Log issues in Issues Log if found
5. Update execution history after running tests

### When Finishing Test Session
1. **Update TEST_PLAN.md completely:**
   - Mark completed tests with ✅
   - Update all status tables
   - Log all issues found
   - Add execution history entry
2. **Clean up:**
   - No temporary files in page folder
   - Archive old reports to `_archive/` if needed
   - Only TEST_PLAN.md + test file in folder

## What NOT to Do

- ❌ Create multiple doc files per page (reports, summaries, etc.)
- ❌ Leave old reports in page folders (archive them)
- ❌ Skip updating TEST_PLAN.md status
- ❌ Create test files without TEST_PLAN.md
- ❌ Mix test files from different pages in one folder

## AI Agent Checklist (MANDATORY)

When working on E2E tests, always:
